  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper, we propose a high order conservative semi-Lagrangian (SL) finite difference Hermite weighted essentially non-oscillatory (HWENO) method for the Vlasov equation based on dimensional splitting. HWENO was first proposed for solving nonlinear hyperbolic problems by evolving both function values and its first derivative values (Qiu and Shu (2004) [23] ). The major advantage of HWENO, compared with the original WENO, lies in its compactness in reconstruction stencils.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
